TASK_TITLE=Smart worker dispatch: restart stale context, delegate relevant context
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_TAGS=agent-defs,skills,shell,dispatch
TASK_TEAM=W3
TASK_DESCRIPTION=When a Manager dispatches a new task to a worker, the system must evaluate whether the worker's existing Claude context is relevant to the new task. If irrelevant — kill the Claude process and relaunch fresh (doey-clear / kill+relaunch). If relevant — delegate into existing context (doey-delegate / send-keys). Currently this is left to ad-hoc judgment. This must be codified in the shipped product so every Doey user gets this behavior out of the box. Update the dispatch skill (doey-dispatch), the Manager agent definition, and/or the relevant shell helpers so that context relevance evaluation is part of the standard dispatch flow. The default should bias toward restart for unrelated work — fresh context produces better results than stale assumptions.
